30/10/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police detained a Croatian citizen on Monday (October 29th) for alleged war crimes against hostages. The 61-year old man is suspected of being a member of the armed unit of the self-proclaimed Republika Srpska Krajina, the short-lived breakaway Serb entity within Croatia. He and three other members of the unit are suspected of having detained a Croatian policeman on June 13th 1991. The police officer has been missing ever since. (Vecernji List, HINA, HRT - 29/10/07)
